					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12566044#post-4371114</guid>
				<title>Co-Author Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12566044/scp-4795#post-4371114</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 21 Sep 2019 17:05:35 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Mew-ltiverse</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5271378</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Floppy was a joy to work with! She was very patient and our ideas worked very well together. ^^</p> <p>So I was searching through the wikimedia commons a few months back and found this picture. I showed it to the team bird members, and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/not-a-seagull" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3009022&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1569085535" alt="not_a_seagull" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3009022)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/not-a-seagull" >not_a_seagull</a></span> helped me brainstorm for it. Months passed, and I never did anything with it.</p> <p>I asked Floppy recently if she wanted to collab, and she said yes! A few weeks later we began brainstorming, and I brought up the idea Seagull had helped me with. Floppy suggested some changes that we both liked, and we got to work!</p> <p>This piece means a lot to me because I wrote a lot of the dialogue, the first two interviews (floppy tweaked the second one by adding some things that only made it better!) and I helped characterize Goshawk and created Nour, which were important later on. Anyone who knows me, knows I’m <em>abysmal</em> with dialogue. But the fact that I was able to write good dialogue on pretty much first try means a lot to me. And, I love what Flopoy did with Nour and Goshawk later on!</p> <p>Idk I ramble, but thanks to Floppy so much for working with me!</p> <p>And of course, thanks to those who crit this. ^^</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
